@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Deblok" where you want 
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  The game board is filled with various horizontal and vertical tiles;
all the horizontal tiles in each row are linked together to form a
'bar'. The same applies for the vertical tiles in each column. To
'unlock' a bar, one tile of that bar must be placed on the game board
edge, where a triangular 'arrow' is located.

  Horizontal tiles on one row can be moved using the corresponding
arrows at the left or right of the game board. Vertical tiles on one
column can be moved using the corresponding upper or lower arrows. If a
tile is located on an arrow, the associated bar can no longer move in
that direction, as the bar is at the limit of its travel.

  If there are tiles of the other type in the way, the choosen bar
cannot move, until the other tiles are moved away. This can get
complicated, as you may have to move many bars in order to move the one
you wanted to move in the first place...

  An unlocked bar indicator, located at the right of the game board
shows how many horizontal and vertical bars have been unlocked. When
there are 8 bars of each type in the indicator, the game is complete.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button
(or with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

  Have fun!

@endnode

